Name: Average SNP count
Description: Number of successfully typed SNP positions averaged over the individuals within a population. This parameter is proportional to the genotyping quality.

Name: Median FST
Description: Median of the FST values distribution associated to each population against all the other populations of the dataset (global value)

Name: Median FST within macro region
Description: Median of the FST values distribution associated to each population against the other populations of the same macro geographic region

Name: Median FST within geographic neighbors
Description: Median of the FST values distribution associated to each population against neighboring populations (minimum 2) within 1000 km radius and excluding drifted populations

Name: Number of neighbors within 1000km
Description: Number of neighbors within a 1000km radius

Name: Ne - Effective population size
Description: Effective population size calculated with software IBDNe corresponding to the harmonic mean of the last 50 generations

Name: Ne - Effective population size 0.05 percentile
Description: Lower 5% confidence interval associated to the effective population size calculations

Name: Ne - Effective population size 0.95 percentile
Description: Upper 5% confidence interval associated to the effective population size calculations

Name: FST
Description: Genetic distance between a pair of populations. Calculated with the Weir and Cockerham formula as implemented in PLINK software. Script available at https://github.com/epifaniarango/Fst_forLargeDatasets

Name: Geographic distance
Description: Geographic distance between population pairs in km. Calculated from population coordinates with rdist.earth package fields in R (https://www.rdocumentation.org/packages/fields/versions/13.3/topics/rdist.earth)

Name: Genetic divergence time
Description: Approximate divergence time calculated from Ne with the formula 2Ne x  linearized FST

Name: Genetic divergence time 0.05 percentile
Description: Lower 5% confidence interval associated to the genetic divergence time

Name: Genetic divergence time 0.95 percentile
Description: Upper 5% confidence interval associated to the genetic divergence time
